<div xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0"><p>This beamtime was allocated to measure the charge density fluctuation excitation in MgB 2 by means of inelastic x-ray scattering. Unfortunately, three weeks before starting the experiment we got the information that our proposed experiment has been very recently performed successfully at the Taiwan beamline BL-12XU of Spring8 by P. Chow et al. Their data clearly show the expected charge density excitation along with a distinct energy dispersion and have been presented at the annual APS meeting 2003. Due to this fact we decided to switch our experimental purpose to the x-ray Raman scattering study of the momentum transfer dependence of the Si L-edge of several Si clathrates. The preliminary results of this experiment are described in report HE-1481 a. Furthermore, we measured the Si L-edge in amorphous SiO using the same experimental setup (See report HE-1481 b).</p></div>
			</abstract>
